title: ujiie_mutsumi
body:
An [i][[iDOLMASTER Cinderella Girls|iDOLM@STER Cinderella Girls]][/i] character in the Cool (Blue Diamond) category. She is 13 and likes books and movies in the adventure genre.

Mutsumi is a soft-spoken girl who wants to live a true adventure. She is always eager to discover the excitements of life that she has read about in her books. Some of her more notable reads include Don Quixote and Indiana Jones. While initially rather aloof, Mutsumi gradually lets herself be a bit wilder after she obtains her first Plus form. body:
A Chinese [[Nijiura Maids|Nijiura Maid]], based on the Hundun (混沌) - one of the Si-xiong (Four Fiends) mentioned in Chinese mythology. As such, she is often seen with fellow Si-xiong maids [[Toukotsu (nijiura maids)|]], [[Toutetsu (nijiura maids)|]] and [[Kyuuki_(nijiura_maid)|Kyuuki]].

Konton appears as a small [[furry]] girl with long [[green hair]] that [[hair over eyes|covers her eyes]]. She has an [[ahoge]] and [[sidelocks]] that hang down in a manner similar to dog ears (like [[Inu-T]]'s hairstyle.) Her body is dog-like and covered with grey/light brown fur, but this is usually hidden under her outfit with the exception of her paws, [[dog tail|tail]], and occasional face fur.

Her maid uniform is a white apron over what appears to be a long-sleeved black [[changpao]] with yellow trim.

In mythology, Hundun represents chaos. It is known as a "faceless beast" and portrayed in some interpretations as a dog, which explains why Konton is a dog girl and her eyes are always hidden.

The [[mynah_(Signalis) | Mynah]] (In reference to the "Myna":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Myna) is a character / unit in the game [[Signalis]].

Mynahs act as the mules of the replika forces employed by the Eusan Nation in the game. They are typically used for heavy duty and hazardous tasks. Such as dealing with dangerous cargo, lethal levels of [[radiation]], heavy machinery and so on. 

Standing at 260cm (8'6"), the MNHR is the tallest replika, even outclassing the [[Falke_(Signalis) | Falke]] and by far most durable one in the Eusan arsenal. Hauling heavy [[power_armor | power armor]], a [[energy_cannon | mining laser]], and accompanied by other corrupted Replika, the Mynah is one of the most dangerous units the player may encounter.

[spoilers] A [[corrupted Mynah (signalis)|]] poses as the first boss in the game. Later on, the player will have to face off against more hostile Mynah units and their accompanying Replika. You will also encounter a friendly but damaged Mynah named [[Beo (signalis)|]].[/spoilers]  

[b]Appearance[/b]

On top of the mentioned [[power_armor | power armor]] and the fact that the Mynah is an [[android]], they have [[blue_eyes | blue eyes]] and [[short_hair | short]] [[black_hair | black hair]] and sometimes are depicted with their face plate lowered, covering their face.

The Kolibri is a character / unit in the game [[Signalis]].

title: chest_stand
body:
A pose where you place your chest on the ground, and curve your back upwards and over until both of your legs are in front of your head.

In Japanese, this is known as the "King Aladdin Impression" (キングアラジンの真似, [i]King Aladdin no Mane[/i]), after King Aladdin, the villain in the first episode of the horror TV drama, "Operation: Mystery!":[http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0195480/releaseinfo] (怪奇大作戦, [i]Kaiki Daisakusen[/i]). In the drama, he rolls away in the chest stand position, and laughing, disappears into the wall as though being plastered into it.

The TV series in itself isn't that well known. However, [[Hyoudou Makoto]], one of the characters in Yuuki Masami's [[Kyuukyoku Choujin R]], does "this pose as his speciality":http://mafactory.com/usersvoice/blogs/master/archive/2007/05/05/429.aspx and so the name became popularised as a result.

More recently, this pose has also been called the [i]Gundam Epyon Mobile Armour Mode[/i]. The [[Gundam Epyon]] in the [[Gundam Wing]] is able to transform into what looks like a two-headed [[dragon]]. This design is meant to be breathtaking when seen from above but from below, you can really understand how it just looks as though it's doing a simple chest stand.

title: honneamise_no_tsubasa
body:
[b]Royal Space Force: The Wings of Honnêamise[/b] [i](Ōritsu Uchūgun: Oneamisu no Tsubasa[/i]) is the first feature-length anime movie produced by [[Gainax]]. Released in 1987, it is directed by Yamaga Hiroyuki with assistant director Akai Takami. The music for the anime film was composed by the late famous musician and actor "Sakamoto Ryuichi":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ryuichi_Sakamoto . [[Sadamoto Yoshiyuki]] designed the characters and [[Anno Hideaki]] worked on it as animation and special effects artist.

The animated film is set in an alternate Earth-like [[alien]] world where an industrial humanoid civilization is flourishing amid an impending war between two bordering nations: the Kingdom of Honneamise and "The Republic". The Kingdom of Honneamise begins the development of an experimental [[space]] program to put the [[astronaut|first man in space]] and thus creates the first [i]Royal Space Force[/i].

This epic [[science fiction]] anime movie would ultimately be a "critically acclaimed Gainax classic":http://www.rogerebert.com/reviews/the-wings-of-honneamise-1995 from the 80s, but it was poorly received and sold only modestly domestically and overseas.

title: frederic_chopin
body:
A Polish composer and virtuoso pianist of French-Polish parentage. He is considered one of the great masters of Romantic music. Chopin was born in Żelazowa Wola, a village in the Duchy of Warsaw. A renowned child-prodigy pianist and composer, Chopin grew up in Warsaw and completed his music education there; he composed many mature works in Warsaw before leaving Poland in 1830 at age 20, shortly before the November 1830 Uprising.

Following the Russian suppression of the Uprising, he settled in Paris as part of Poland's Great Emigration. During the remaining 19 years of his life, Chopin gave only some 30 public performances, preferring the more intimate atmosphere of the salon; he supported himself by sales of his compositions and as a piano teacher. After some romantic dalliances with Polish women, including an abortive engagement, from 1837 to 1847 he carried on a relationship with the French writer Amantine Dupin. For most of his life, Chopin suffered from poor health; he died in Paris in 1849 at age 39.
 
The vast majority of Chopin's works are for solo piano, though he also wrote two piano concertos, a few chamber pieces and some songs to Polish texts. His piano works are often technically demanding, with an emphasis on nuance and expressive depth. Chopin invented the instrumental ballade and made major innovations to the piano sonata, mazurka, waltz, nocturne, polonaise, étude, impromptu, scherzo and prélude.

Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice is a 2016 American superhero film based on the DC Comics characters Batman and Superman. Produced by Warner Bros. Pictures, it is a follow-up to the 2013 film [[Man of Steel]] and the second film in the [[DC Extended Universe]] (DCEU). The film was directed by [[Zack Snyder]], written by Chris Terrio and David S. Goyer, and features an ensemble cast that includes [[Ben Affleck]] as Batman and Henry Cavill as Superman. 

Batman v Superman: Dawn of Justice is the first live-action film to feature Batman and Superman together, as well as the first live-action cinematic portrayal of [[Wonder Woman]]. In the film, criminal mastermind [[Lex Luthor]] manipulates Batman into a preemptive battle with Superman, who Luthor is obsessed with destroying.

The [b]protect gear[/b] is used by personnel of the Japanese Capital Police Special Unit "Kerberos" (also known as "Panzer Cops"), who are [[weapon|armed]] with [[MG42]] [[machine gun|machine guns]] (originally [[MG34]]'s in [[akai megane|The Red Spectacles]]). 

The design is clearly inspired by the soldiers of [[nazi|Nazi Germany]] during [[World War II]] (as well as the [i]Stormtroopers[/i] of [[german empire|Imperial Germany]] in [[World War I]]), and has influenced quite a lot of fictional soldier designs, such as [[Killzone]], [[ncr veteran ranger|Fallout]], [[wolfenstein (series)|Wolfenstein]], and even "Scooby-doo":[https://scoobydoo.fandom.com/wiki/Kriegstaffebot].

title: f-16_fighting_falcon
body:
The [b]General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon[/b] is a multirole [[jet]] fighter aircraft originally developed by General Dynamics for the United States Air Force (USAF). 

Designed as an air superiority day fighter, it evolved into a successful all-weather multirole aircraft. Over 4,500 aircraft have been built since production was approved in 1976. Although no longer being purchased by the U.S. Air Force, improved versions are still being built for export customers. 

In 1993, General Dynamics sold its aircraft manufacturing business to the Lockheed Corporation, which in turn became part of Lockheed Martin after a 1995 merger with Martin Marietta.

The Fighting Falcon is a fighter with numerous innovations including a frameless bubble canopy for better visibility, side-mounted control stick to ease control while maneuvering, a seat reclined 30 degrees to reduce the effect of g-forces on the pilot, and the first use of a relaxed static stability/fly-by-wire flight control system that makes it a highly nimble aircraft. 

The F-16 has an internal M61 Vulcan cannon and 11 locations for mounting weapons and other mission equipment. The F-16's official name is "Fighting Falcon", but "Viper" is commonly used by its pilots, due to a perceived resemblance to a viper snake as well as the [[Battlestar Galactica]] [[viper_(spacecraft)|Colonial Viper]] starfighter.

In addition to active duty U.S. Air Force, Air Force Reserve Command, and Air National Guard units, the aircraft is also used by the USAF aerial demonstration team, the U.S. Air Force Thunderbirds, and as an adversary/aggressor aircraft by the United States Navy. The F-16 has also been procured to serve in the air forces of 25 other nations. It served as the basis for the development of the Mitsubishi [[Mitsubishi f-2]] jet fighter from [[Japan]].

title: mitsubishi_f-2
body:
The Mitsubishi F-2 is a multirole fighter derived from the General Dynamics F-16 Fighting Falcon, and manufactured by Mitsubishi Heavy Industries and Lockheed Martin for the [[Japan Air Self-Defense Force]], with a 60/40 split in manufacturing between [[Japan]] and the [[United states|United States]].

The basis of the F-2's design is the [[f-16_fighting_falcon|F-16]] Agile Falcon, an unsuccessful offer by General Dynamics to provide a low-cost alternative for the Advanced Tactical Fighter (ATF) competition. 

Production started in 1996 and the first [[aircraft]] entered service in 2000. The first 76 aircraft entered service by 2008, with a total of 98 airframes produced. The first active electronically scanned array (AESA) radar on a combat aircraft was the J/APG-1 introduced on the Mitsubishi F-2 in 1995.

The F-2 is nicknamed "Viper Zero", a reference to the [[f-16_fighting_falcon|F-16]]'s unofficial nickname of "Viper" and the [[A6M Zero|Mitsubishi A6M Zero]].

title: labelcase
body:
A minor NPC in [[Toushin Toshi II]], and a boss character in its remake, [[Toushin Toshi Girls Gift]].

In the original game, Labelcase is a timid [[angel]] who is easily frightened. In Girl's Gift, however, her character is completely overhauled, transforming her into an Angel Knight with a stoic, but strong-willed, personality. She also now possesses the epithet "Bow Angel," after the bow she wields in battle.

In the original game, she has [[short hair|short]], [[blue hair]] and [[red eyes]], with a large red [[crystal]] in her forehead. She possesses a pair of [[angel wings]] and wears a [[yellow shirt]] with a [[yellow skirt]], with a gap exposing her midriff. In Girls Gift, her design is largely the same, except her skirt and top are now white, and she wears blue [[elbow gloves]] and a [[halterneck]]. Her eyes have also been recolored to blue, and her top exposes far more [[cleavage]].

In both games, she is notable for bearing a strong resemblance to the [[Kalar (race)|]] race.

title: cardinal_(animal)
body:
The northern cardinal, simply called a cardinal in North America, is a medium-sized [[bird|songbird]] native to North and Central America.  Named after the cardinals of the Roman Catholic Church who wear distinct red robes and caps.  The male cardinal features vibrant crimson red feathers and a distinct black "mask" around the eyes and beak.  Female cardinals are mostly grayish brown with tinges of red, and have a less distinct gray to black "mask" around the eyes and beak.  Both males and females have a coral colored beak and prominent raised crest of feathers on their head.

title: kadomatsu
body:
A [b]kadomatsu[/b] (literally "gate pine") is a traditional Japanese decoration of the [[New Year]] placed in pairs in front of homes to welcome ancestral spirits or [i]kami[/i] of the harvest. They are placed after [[Christmas]] until January 7 (or January 15 during the Edo period) and are considered temporary housing ("[i]shintai[/i]":https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shintai) for [i]kami[/i]. Designs for [i]kadomatsu[/i] vary depending on region but are typically made of [[pine_tree|pine]], [[bamboo]], and sometimes ume tree sprigs which represent longevity, prosperity and steadfastness, respectively.

A [i]frisbee[/i], or [i]flying disc [/i], is disc-shaped [[toy]], generally about 20-25 cm (8-10 inches) in diameter and usually made of plastic, that is thrown with a flick of the wrist. A circumferential lip and airfoil cross-section enable the disc to glide farther by generating lift as it rotates. The name [i]Frisbee[/i] itself is a trademark of toy manufacturer Wham-O.  The name [i]Frisbee[/i] (though altered to avoid trademark infringement) is based on the name Frisbie Pie Company, a company whose pie tins had their name stamped on it and were already being used as improvised flying disc toy referred to as a "Frisbie" by kids and college students.

title: beaver
body:
Large semiaquatic rodents that are native to the the Northern Hemisphere.  Two species of beaver exist, the North American beaver and Eurasian beaver.  Beavers are the second-largest rodents in the world after [[capybara]]s.  Beavers have stout bodies with large heads, long chisel-like incisors, brown or gray fur, hand-like front feet, webbed back feet, and tails that are flat and scaly.

Beavers are consider a keystone species, as they can greatly influence an ecosystem through their construction of dams and lodges from tree branches, vegetation, rocks and mud.  These dams restrict water flow and create wetlands for which other animals and plants may depend on.

title: tomato
body:
Considered a [[vegetable]], particularly for culinary purposes, the tomato is botanically a [[fruit]] produced by the plant [i]Solanum lycopersicum[/i] of the nightshade family.

The word "tomato" comes from the ancient Nahuatl word [i]tomatl[/i].

In the US, the US Supreme Court ruled in the 1893 case Nix v. Hedden that the tomato is legally classified as a vegetable.  This was to resolve an issue with the Tariff Act of 1883 which required a tax be paid on imported vegetables, but not fruits.

title: hang-on
body:
[b]Hang-On[/b] (ハングオン [i]Hanogu Onu[/i]) is an arcade game released by [[Sega]] in 1985. It was designed by "Suzuki Yu":http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Yu_Suzuki and is considered "the world's first full-body-experience" [[video game]], since its cabinet had the shape of a motorcycle and moved according to the action seen on-screen. 

In the game, the player controls a racing [[motorcycle]] against time and other computer controlled bikes. It was one of the first arcade games to use 16 bit graphics and Sega's "Super Scaler" technology that allowed pseudo 3D sprite scaling at high frame rates. 

The game was also built into some versions of the [[Sega Master System]]. A sequel called [i]Super Hang-On[/i] was ported to the [[Sega Mega Drive]]. 

The title is derived from when the biker is turning and has to "hang on" to the bike while the bike is leaning, which Suzuki had read in a Japanese bike magazine, though Suzuki learnt later the technique was called "hang off" in North America. Nevertheless, he chose to keep the former name.

title: flamingo
body:
Any of several aquatic birds of the family Phoenicopteridae, having very long legs and neck, webbed feet, a bill bent downward at the tip, and pinkish to scarlet plumage.

Flamingos are filter-feeders and famously derive their color from the aqueous bacteria in their diet. Captive flamingos which are given insufficient amounts of carotene may turn pale pink or white.

h4. See also
* [[Tag Group:Birds]]

title: orangutan
body:
A large mainly solitary arboreal great [[ape]] with long reddish brown hair, long arms, and hooked hands and feet, native to Borneo and Sumatra, [[Indonesia]]. The mature male develops fleshy cheek pads and a throat pouch. Orangutans eat an omnivorous diet consisting of fruit, foliage, eggs, insects, and small animals. They are also known to consume soil on occasion (geophagy).

Classified in the genus Pongo, orangutans were originally considered to be one species. From 1996, they were divided into two species: the Bornean orangutan ([i]P. pygmaeus[/i], with three subspecies) and the Sumatran orangutan ([i]P. abelii[/i]). A third species, the Tapanuli orangutan ([i]P. tapanuliensis[/i]), was identified definitively in 2017. The orangutans are the only surviving species of the subfamily Ponginae, which diverged genetically from the other hominids ([[gorilla]]s, [[chimpanzee]]s, and humans) between 19.3 and 15.7 million years ago.

title: fn_model_1910
body:
The [b]FN Model 1910[/b] or M1910 is a blowback-operated semi-automatic [b][[handgun]][/b] designed by [[John Moses Browning]] and produced by [[FN Herstal]] from 1910 to 1983, chambered for .32 or .380 ACP cartridge. Visually identifiable by its lack of external hammer, grip panels with rounded top and often FN logo embossed on them, as well as [[M1911]]-like trigger. 

It was the [[gun]] used by Gavrilo Princip to assassinate Archduke Franz Ferdinand of Austria and his wife in Sarajevo on 28 June 1914. This tag can also apply to its larger variant, the Model 1922.

title: twitter_sample
body:
A image from Twitter that is an [[image sample]], rather than the original image.

Original images end with [code]:orig[/code]. Sample images don't.

To avoid uploading a sample, paste a link to the image on the upload page, rather than downloading the image to your computer then uploading it.

In addition to images tagged with this tag, any image that matches either of the following queries are also treated as twitter samples, given that they are [i]visually identical[/i]:

* {{source:*twitter.com/ md5_mismatch -upscaled status:active}}
* {{source:*pbs.twimg.com/ md5_mismatch -upscaled status:active}}

Make sure they are fairly identical to the original image, however. Sometimes the source might be incorrect. This doesn't factor in edits such as post #2440268.

h4. Examples

* Sample: https://pbs.twimg.com/media/C2uQastUQAE5nyc.jpg (900x1200)
* Original: https://pbs.twimg.com/media/C2uQastUQAE5nyc.jpg:orig (1200x1600)

title: manchukuo_flag
body:
The flag used by Manchukuo between 1932 and 1945. The flag features the "Five Races Under One Union" motif borrowed from the Beiyang goverments flag. The colours represent the five largest ethnic groups living in Manchuria (Manchukuo):
Yellow represents the Manchu people
Red represents the Han Chinese 
Blue represents the Mongol
White represents the Hui people
Black represents the Koreans

This tag should be used for posts featuring Manchukuo's flag. Posts using the colors in the style of the Beiyang flag may also be tagged.

title: battle_of_the_philippine_sea
body:
[b]The Battle of the Philippine Sea[/b] (June 19–20, 1944) was a major naval battle of [[World War II]] that eliminated the [[Imperial Japanese Navy]]'s ability to conduct large-scale [[aircraft carrier]] operations. 

It took place during the [[United States]]' amphibious invasion of the Mariana Islands during the Pacific War. The battle was the last of five major "carrier-versus-carrier" engagements between American and [[Japan]]ese naval forces, and pitted elements of the [[United States Navy]]'s Fifth Fleet against ships and aircraft of the Imperial Japanese Navy's Mobile Fleet and nearby island garrisons. 

This was the largest carrier-to-carrier battle in history, involving 24 aircraft carriers, deploying roughly 1,350 carrier-based aircraft. It ended in a decisive Allied [[victory]]. The Japanese aircraft carrier [[shoukaku_(aircraft_carrier)|Shoukaku]] was sunk during this battle.

title: akuma_(street_fighter)
body:
[b]Akuma[/b], known as [b]Gouki[/b] in the Japanese version, is a popular fighter in the [[Street Fighter]] series.

Originally appearing in [[Street Fighter II (series)|Street Fighter II Turbo]] as a secret character and hidden boss, He is [[Gouken]]'s younger brother and [[Ryu (street fighter)|]]'s adoptive uncle. He has red hair, wears prayer beads around his neck, and wears a black gi (occasionally displayed as blue in artwork). The [[heaven (kanji)|kanji 'Ten']] (天) - meaning "sky", "heaven", or "providence" - can be seen on his back when it appears during certain victory poses.

A morally complex character, Akuma helds the belief that an evil energy known as Satsui no Hado ("Surge of murderous intent") is necessary to unlock one's true potential. Proclaiming himself to be "The Master of the Fist", Akuma travels around the world to find a worthy opponent and kill them in a fight to prove his strength.

While he seems to have no remorse in killing anyone (viewing them as weaker opponents who are "worthy" enough to be killed by him), he is easily offended when someone tries to harm helpless people (especially children) and will not hesitate to kill the attacker. He is also known to hold back his power when his opponent is not "ready" for the fight, such as against [[Kasugano Sakura|an inexperienced Sakura]] or a [[Gen (street fighter)|terminally ill Gen]].

title: ankokuboshi_kurome
body:
The main antagonist and true mastermind behind all of the events in [[Shin Jigen Game Neptune VII|Megadimension Neptunia VII.]] 

[spoiler]This is the original [[Tennouboshi Uzume|Uzume Tennouboshi]], nicknamed Kurome Ankokuboshi by both the regular and [[Adult Neptune|older Neptune]]. She was the Console Patron Unit (CPU) of Planeptune before Uranus and [[Neptune (neptunia)|Neptune]]. However, she sealed herself away because she could not control her powers. Coming to hate Gamindustri, the source of her power shifted from Share Energy to Negative Energy. Becoming consumed by the Negative Energy, she desired to break free from her seal to have her revenge. Her remaining Share Energy eventually split from her and took on the form of another Uzume Tennouboshi.[/spoiler]

Technically, her true name is "[spoiler]Tennouboshi Uzume[/spoiler]" and "Ankokuboshi Kurome" is just a nickname that [[Adult Neptune]] came up with and the other characters also started using.

Voiced by: [spoiler][[Honda Mariko]] (Japanese), [[Erica Lindbeck]] (English)[/spoiler]

title: ring_fit_adventure
body:
An [[exercising|exercising]] action/role-playing game for the [[Nintendo Switch]].

The game comes with two accessories: the [[Ring-Con]], a Pilates ring that the user holds and one [[Joy-Con]] slots into, and the Leg Strap, a [[thigh strap]] that holds the other Joy-Con.

The game's main mode is a turn-based role-playing game, where progress is based on performing physical activities using the Ring-Con and Leg Strap. Other modes include fitness routines and party games. 

The game is popular with [[virtual YouTuber]]s for the fan service it provides.
